        main: "\"Love one another, but make not a bond of love: Let it rather be a moving sea between the shores of your souls.\" <br> - Kahlil Gibran<br><br>When the Six of Hearts appears in your cartomancy reading, it indicates great harmony, balance, and alignment within your relationships, both personal and otherwise. This card heralds a time of ease, flow, and emotional abundance. Relationships are impactful, deep, and easy at this time.<br><br>Oftentimes, relationships can be tumultuous. They can be very nuanced and can hold much duality. We can love someone while also feeling the frequency of hate on occasion. Someone can make us feel confident and seen in one moment, and then small or insignificant in the next. Relationships can be very complicated, and this is by design. After all, our relationships with others are our greatest teachers in the School of Life!<br><br>Our relationships mirror aspects of ourselves back to us—the light, the dark, and everything in between. This, of course, can instigate a whole gamut of emotions. However, during this moment in time, your relationships are harmonious and healthy. You have likely healed deeply on the emotional level from relationships that were in your life to be a catalyst for healing and growth.<br><br>When the Six of Hearts appears, it also signals that you may be experiencing a period of reminiscence, where you are nostalgic for the past and how certain relationships made you feel. Perhaps you're remembering a courtship with your beloved who, now 15 years and three kids later, you still love, and yet find yourself longing for or reminiscing about the early days—the innocence, the freedom, and the pure joy of it all.<br><br>These fond memories are beautiful, and while it's always enriching to recall them with love, you are reminded to enjoy them without attachment. Recognize their ephemeral nature and don't let them distract you from what is happening in the present moment.<br><br>If there are old wounds that are triggered by these old memories, know that they are coming back to the surface to be healed. You are constantly co-creating a better reality in the here and now. In the now is where you heal, and in the now is where you create what is yet to come. The wisdom of this card asks you to revisit the past with non-attachment, allowing yourself to learn from past hurts or mistakes and to look with gratitude on everything that has brought you to where you are now.", 
        action: "We oftentimes find ourselves taking a proverbial “trip down Memory Lane,” and when we do, we need to visit the past without lingering too long. Sometimes we long for the past because it was just so good. Other times, we linger in past memories as a form of self-punishment as we play out all of our regrets. <br><br>During these times, there is a beautiful mantra called the Ho'oponopono mantra that you can use to assist you in letting go of burdens that are keeping you stuck in the past, and preventing you from living the life you desire.<br>It is a short mantra you can repeat anytime you find yourself dwelling in the past and getting wrapped up in the emotional current of scenarios that have already transpired. It goes like this:<br><br>The Ho’oponopono Mantra:<br>    I love you.<br>    I am sorry.<br>    Please forgive me.<br>    Thank you.<br>This beautiful mantra is simple yet powerful, working as a complete system for emotional alignment just as the 6 of Hearts suggests—taking responsibility for our emotional state, healing old rifts, expressing gratitude, and returning to love as our foundation. Both the mantra and the card remind us that true emotional harmony begins within ourselves before extending to our relationships with others!<br>"
